Interview Explanation (How to Answer)
In production, I prefer Reserved Instances for predictable workloads. For this setup, a 3-year Reserved Instance gives the best cost optimization, reducing costs by nearly 60% compared to Pay-As-You-Go while maintaining full performance. Premium SSDs are used to ensure consistent IOPS and low latency for production workloads.
FinOps & Architecture Best Practices
- Use 3-Year Reserved Instances for stable PROD workloads
- Enable Availability Zones for high availability (no extra VM cost)
- Monitor Log Analytics ingestion to avoid unexpected costs
- Right-size VMs periodically using Azure Advisor


